docs.abstract: The survey would bring heavy trucks looking for signs of oil reserves into one of the most remote and pristine parts of the United States.
docs.snippet: The survey would bring heavy trucks looking for signs of oil reserves into one of the most remote and pristine parts of the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump administration has relaunched long-delayed plans to conduct a seismic survey in the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge in Alaska as a prelude to drilling for oil there.

headline.main: White House Releases New Plan for Seismic Tests in Arctic Refuge
headline.print_headline: Seismic Tests Are Planned for Arctic Refuge

docs.abstract: The Los Angeles dealer David Kordansky is using this moment to get more serious about helping and hiring people “left out of the conversation.”
docs.snippet: The Los Angeles dealer David Kordansky is using this moment to get more serious about helping and hiring people “left out of the conversation.”
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — David Kordansky keeps one of Bob Weir’s guitars and Jerry Garcia’s amplifiers in the office of his gallery here in Mid-City. Love of the Grateful Dead, says the artist Mary Weatherford, helps explain Mr. Kordansky’s approach to being an art dealer. “The Grateful Dead is how Kordansky thinks,” she said. “There is a structure, but within the structure is improvisation.”

headline.main: With Black Artists’ Input, One Gallery Is ‘Starting to Look Different’
headline.print_headline: In Pursuit of a More Diverse Gallery

docs.abstract: Glossy magazines are going digital. Brands are shutting down. The fantasy images of women in ball gowns with elephants may soon be no more.
docs.snippet: Glossy magazines are going digital. Brands are shutting down. The fantasy images of women in ball gowns with elephants may soon be no more.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the 1930s and ’40s, when the photographer Louise Dahl-Wolfe took models out of the studio and onto location — shooting them poolside for Harper’s Bazaar, say — she was making pictures about freedom, about women’s changing role in society, about travel and leisure culture.

headline.main: Can Fashion Photography Survive the Pandemic?
headline.print_headline: Can Fashion Photography  Survive the Pandemic?

docs.abstract: An independent investigation found no mistreatment of a Black curator, Chaédria LaBouvier, but the chief curator, Nancy Spector, who is white, is leaving after 34 years.
docs.snippet: An independent investigation found no mistreatment of a Black curator, Chaédria LaBouvier, but the chief curator, Nancy Spector, who is white, is leaving after 34 years.
docs.lead_paragraph: An independent investigation into how the Guggenheim Museum handled last year’s exhibition on the artist Jean-Michel Basquiat has concluded there is no evidence that the show’s guest curator, Chaédria LaBouvier, who is Black, “was subject to adverse treatment on the basis of her race,” the museum announced on Thursday.

headline.main: Guggenheim’s Top Curator Is Out as Inquiry Into Basquiat Show Ends
headline.print_headline: Guggenheim’s Top Curator  Is Leaving  The Museum After an Inquiry

docs.abstract: New York City, Seattle and Portland, Ore., all so-called “anarchist jurisdictions,” are trying to stop the Trump administration from withholding federal funds.
docs.snippet: New York City, Seattle and Portland, Ore., all so-called “anarchist jurisdictions,” are trying to stop the Trump administration from withholding federal funds.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump administration’s attempt to strip New York City of federal funds because the administration viewed it as an “anarchist jurisdiction” could cost the city as much as $12 billion — money for the cash-starved subway, for the Police Department and for the city’s efforts to treat coronavirus patients, city officials said on Thursday.

headline.main: With Billions at Stake, New York Sues Trump Over ‘Anarchist’ Label

docs.abstract: His proposed solution to addressing both urgent calls for police reform and animosity from law enforcement toward Democrats is one he’s long relied on: He’ll just get everyone in the same room.
docs.snippet: His proposed solution to addressing both urgent calls for police reform and animosity from law enforcement toward Democrats is one he’s long relied on: He’ll just get everyone in the same room.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bill Johnson knew, before he reached out to Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s campaign last spring, that things had changed between the former vice president and the nation’s police unions. A once-close alliance had frayed amid clashes over police brutality and racism in the justice system. Still, Mr. Johnson, the executive director of the National Association of Police Organizations, invited Mr. Biden to address the group as it weighed its 2020 endorsement.

headline.main: Joe Biden Had Close Ties With Police Leaders. Will They Help Him Now?
headline.print_headline: A Frayed Bond Between Biden And the Police

docs.abstract: Covid-19 Essentials may be the country’s first retail chain dedicated solely to products required because of an infectious disease.

docs.lead_paragraph: LONE TREE, Colo. — Darcy Velasquez and her mother, Roberta Truax, were walking recently in the Park Meadows mall about 15 miles south of downtown Denver, looking for Christmas gifts for Ms. Velasquez’s two children, when they spotted a store with a display of rhinestone-studded masks.

headline.main: Need to Find a Pandemic Necessity? There’s Now a Store for That
headline.print_headline: As the Pandemic Persists, Retailer Meets Demand  For Stylish Face Masks

docs.abstract: The beloved crime novelist has written a western-inflected mystery with her first American protagonist and a back story that touches on police violence and systemic racism.
docs.snippet: The beloved crime novelist has written a western-inflected mystery with her first American protagonist and a back story that touches on police violence and systemic racism.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ever since she released her debut novel, “In the Woods,” Tana French has drawn such a devoted following that it borders on cultish. In the last 13 years, she has published seven novels that won over millions of fans with their twisty, nuanced plots.

headline.main: With ‘The Searcher,’ Tana French Ventures Into New Territory
headline.print_headline: A Novelist Ventures Into New Territory
